From Wiktionary, the free dictionary

Spanish

[edit]

Alternative forms

[edit]
  • enjaguar

Etymology

[edit]

Inherited from Old Spanish enxaguar (with metathesis of /w/), from Vulgar Latin *exaquāre (+ the Spanish prefix en-), a verb based on Latin ex- (“out”) + aqua (“water”).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /enxwaˈɡaɾ/ [ẽŋ.xwaˈɣ̞aɾ]
  • Rhymes: -aɾ
  • Syllabification: en‧jua‧gar

Verb

[edit]

enjuagar (first-person singular present enjuago, first-person singular preterite enjuagué, past participle enjuagado)

  1. (transitive) to rinse
